text: Honey Creek is a stream in Pottawattamie and Harrison counties, Iowa, in the United States. It is a tributary of Missouri River. The stream headwaters are at and the confluence with the Missouri is at . Honey Creek was named by settlers for the great number of honeybees seen at the creek. ==See also== *List of rivers of Iowa ==References== Category:Rivers of Harrison County, Iowa Category:Rivers of Pottawattamie County, Iowa Category:Rivers of Iowa
